<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="469" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d469">
                                    <note rend="inline" type="source">
                                        <persName corresp="#p_HA1">Hiss</persName> Collection</note>
                                    <head>
                                        <hi rend="italic">United States Delegation Draft Memorandum
                                            Regarding Invitation to Saudi Arabia to Attend the
                                            United Nations Conference</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d469fn1">Handwritten in pencil; authorship not
                                            indicated. Text is crossed out, apparently in view of
                                            the notation at the top. Saudi Arabia, however, did
                                            adhere to the Declaration by United Nations on March 1,
                                            1945, and was represented at the San Francisco
                                            Conference.</note>
                                    </head>
                                    <opener>
                                        <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Yalta</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-11">Feb.
                                                11</date>
                                        </dateline>
                                    </opener>
                                    <p rend="flushleft">(Copy)</p>
                                    <p rend="center">R’s<note n="2" xml:id="d469fn2">Russians.</note> refused to agree</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. <persName>Early</persName></hi>:
                                        Please inform the President on behalf of Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SERJ1">Stettinius</persName> that at today’s
                                        final meeting of the Foreign Ministers held shortly after
                                        the President left, Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> proposed and Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> and Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SERJ1">Stettinius</persName><note n="3" xml:id="d469fn3">The handwriting to this point is that
                                            of Hiss; the handwriting of the remainder has not been
                                            identified.</note> agreed that Saudi Arabia be added to
                                        the eight associated nations and Turkey as entitled to be
                                        invited to the United Nations Conference on April 25 at San
                                        Francisco if they declare war by March 1.</p>
                                    <p>We consider this as a desirable move and suggest that the
                                        President should inform <persName corresp="#p_SI1">Ibn</persName> Saud of this when the two meet in the
                                        next few days.</p>
                                    <p>In any event <persName>Colonel</persName>
                                        <persName corresp="#p_ECWA1">Eddy</persName>, our Minister
                                        who will accompany <persName corresp="#p_SI1">Ibn</persName>
                                        Saud to the Quincy, should be informed of this and should
                                        inform <persName corresp="#p_SI1">Ibn</persName>.</p>
                                    <p>Will you please give the above information also to Admiral
                                            <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> &amp; to
                                        Admiral <persName corresp="#p_BW1">Brown</persName>
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                                </body></text></TEI>